				"verses": [
					{
						"extra": false,
						"text": "All over the world at the end of day,\nHeav&rsquo;nly Father&rsquo;s children kneel down and pray,\nEach saying thank you in his own special way,\nSaying thank you, thank you in his own special way.\n&ldquo;Gracias.&rdquo; <em>(grah-see-ahs)</em> &ldquo;Malo.&rdquo; <em>(mah-loh)</em> &ldquo;Wir danken dir.&rdquo; <em>(veer don-ken deer)</em>\nAll over the world tender voices hear.\nSome say &ldquo;tak,&rdquo; <em>(tahk)</em> others &ldquo;merci,&rdquo; <em>(mare-see)</em>\n&ldquo;Kansha shimasu,&rdquo; <em>(kahn-shah shee-mah-sue)</em> we thank thee.\nOur Heavenly Father hears them;\nHe understands each tongue.\nOur Heav&rsquo;nly Father knows them;\nHe loves them, loves them, ev&rsquo;ry one.",
						"type": "verse"
					},
					{
						"extra": false,
						"text": "Non-English words for <em>thank you:</em>\nSpanish: <em>gracias</em>\nTongan: <em>mālō</em>\nGerman: <em>wir danken dir</em>\nDanish: <em>tak</em>\nFrench: <em>merci</em>\nJapanese: <em>kansha shimasu</em>",
						"type": "other"
					}
				]
