				"uri": "/manual/childrens-songbook/when-he-comes-again",
				"verses": [
					{
						"extra": false,
						"text": "I wonder, when he comes again,\nWill herald angels sing?\nWill earth be white with drifted snow,\nOr will the world know spring?\nI wonder if one star will shine\nFar brighter than the rest;\nWill daylight stay the whole night through?\nWill songbirds leave their nests?\nI&rsquo;m sure he&rsquo;ll call his little ones\nTogether &rsquo;round his knee,\nBecause he said in days gone by,\n&ldquo;Suffer them to come to me.&rdquo;",
						"type": "verse"
					},
					{
						"extra": false,
						"text": "I wonder, when he comes again,\nWill I be ready there\nTo look upon his loving face\nAnd join with him in prayer?\nEach day I&rsquo;ll try to do his will\nAnd let my light so shine\nThat others seeing me may seek\nFor greater light divine.\nThen, when that blessed day is here,\nHe&rsquo;ll love me and he&rsquo;ll say,\n&ldquo;You&rsquo;ve served me well, my little child;\nCome unto my arms to stay.&rdquo;",
						"type": "verse"
					}
				]
