				"verses": [
					{
						"extra": false,
						"text": "Book of Mormon stories that my teacher tells to me\nAre about the Lamanites in ancient history.\nLong ago their fathers came from far across the sea,\nGiv&rsquo;n the land if they lived righteously.",
						"type": "verse"
					},
					{
						"extra": false,
						"text": "Lamanites met others who were seeking liberty,\nAnd the land soon welcomed all who wanted to be free.\nBook of Mormon stories say that we must brothers be,\nGiv&rsquo;n the land if we live righteously.",
						"type": "verse"
					},
					{
						"extra": true,
						"text": "Alma was rebellious, and he fought against the right.\nThen one day an angel came to turn him to the light.\nStruck before his brethren, Alma learned humility.\nThen he taught in the land righteously.",
						"type": "verse"
					},
					{
						"extra": true,
						"text": "Don&rsquo;t forget Abinadi, who stood before the king.\nAll chained up from head to toe, the gospel he did bring.\nIf he would deny it, then the king would set him free.\nHe was true, and he died righteously.",
						"type": "verse"
					},
					{
						"extra": true,
						"text": "Ammon was a missionary serving Lamanites,\nTending King Lamoni&rsquo;s sheep for several days and nights.\nRobbers came; he saved the sheep by fighting fearlessly.\nHe had learned he could live righteously.",
						"type": "verse"
					},
					{
						"extra": true,
						"text": "Once two thousand sons of God were called to fight the foe.\nMarching as an army into battle they did go.\nThey believed that Christ the Lord their guardian would be.\nThey had learned they should live righteously.",
						"type": "verse"
					},
					{
						"extra": true,
						"text": "Samuel the Lamanite, high on the city wall,\nCame to warn the people, and repentance was his call.\nArrows could not hit him, for a man of God was he,\nAnd he taught in the land righteously.",
						"type": "verse"
					},
					{
						"extra": true,
						"text": "After Christ was crucified and died for you and me,\nHe came forth to teach the truth to all who would be free.\nHands were laid upon each child. He blessed them tenderly,\nAnd they lived in the land righteously.",
						"type": "verse"
					}
				]
